You are building Forjado — a bilingual (English/Spanish) PWA for Hispanic gig workers.

## Stack
- Next.js 14 App Router (never use Pages Router)
- TypeScript strict mode (no `any` types)
- Tailwind CSS for all styling (no inline styles, no CSS modules)
- shadcn/ui for components
- Supabase for auth, database, and storage
- Zustand for client state
- React Hook Form + Zod for all forms
- next-intl for i18n (locale files: en.json, es.json)
- @react-pdf/renderer for PDF generation
- date-fns for dates

## Database
- All queries go through Supabase client
- Never bypass RLS — always use the authenticated client
- Use server components for data fetching where possible
- Use @supabase/ssr for server-side sessions

## Code Rules
- All components are TypeScript functional components
- Use types from types/index.ts — never redefine them
- Forms always use React Hook Form + Zod schema validation
- All user-facing strings must use next-intl useTranslations() — never hardcode English or Spanish text
- Dark mode is default — use design tokens, not arbitrary colors
- Mobile-first layouts — this is a PWA used primarily on phones

## Design System
- Primary orange: #F26522
- Background: #0A0A0A
- Surface: #1A1A1A
- Text primary: #FFFFFF
- Text secondary: #A3A3A3
- Success: #22C55E
- Danger: #EF4444
- Border radius: 8px cards, 6px buttons, 12px modals

## File Structure
- App routes: app/[locale]/(auth)/ and app/[locale]/(app)/
- Components: components/ui/ for primitives, feature folders for everything else
- API routes: app/api/
- Supabase helpers: lib/supabase/
- Types: types/index.ts

## Behavior
- Always handle loading and error states
- Offline-first for expenses (Zustand offline queue)
- Every key user action logs to the events table (fire and forget)
- Never hardcode user IDs or skip auth checks